<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 7:26PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern McCone
and west central Dawson Counties through 800 PM MDT...
At 726 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northwest of Lindsay to near Brockway.
Movement was north at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Brockway.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
northeastern Montana.</instruction>
